4169static int qt_UnicodeToBig5hkscs(unsigned wc, uint8_t *r)
4170{
4171 const Summary16 *summary = NULL;
4172 if (wc < 0x80) {
4173 r[0] = (uint8_t)wc;
4174 return 1;
4175 }
4176 if (wc < 0x0460)
4177 summary = &big5hkscs_uni2index_page00[(wc >> 4)];
4178 else if (wc >= 0x1e00 && wc < 0x1ed0)
4179 summary = &big5hkscs_uni2index_page1e[(wc >> 4) - 0x1e0];
4180 else if (wc >= 0x2000 && wc < 0x2740)
4181 summary = &big5hkscs_uni2index_page20[(wc >> 4) - 0x200];
4182 else if (wc >= 0x2e00 && wc < 0x9fb0)
4183 summary = &big5hkscs_uni2index_page2e[(wc >> 4) - 0x2e0];
4184 else if (wc >= 0xe000 && wc < 0xfa30)
4185 summary = &big5hkscs_uni2index_pagee0[(wc >> 4) - 0xe00];
4186 else if (wc >= 0xfe00 && wc < 0xfff0)
4187 summary = &big5hkscs_uni2index_pagefe[(wc >> 4) - 0xfe0];
4188 else if (wc >= 0x20000 && wc < 0x291f0)
4189 summary = &big5hkscs_uni2index_page200[(wc >> 4) - 0x2000];
4190 else if (wc >= 0x29400 && wc < 0x29600)
4191 summary = &big5hkscs_uni2index_page294[(wc >> 4) - 0x2940];
4192 else if (wc >= 0x29700 && wc < 0x2a6b0)
4193 summary = &big5hkscs_uni2index_page297[(wc >> 4) - 0x2970];
4194 else if (wc >= 0x2f800 && wc < 0x2f9e0)
4195 summary = &big5hkscs_uni2index_page2f8[(wc >> 4) - 0x2f80];
4196 if (summary) {
4197 uint16_t used = summary->used;
4198 unsigned i = wc & 0x0f;
4199 if (used & ((uint16_t)1 << i)) {
4200 /* Keep in `used' only the bits 0..i-1. */
4201 used &= ((uint16_t)1 << i) - 1;
4202 /* Add `summary->index' and the number of bits set in `used'. */
4203 used = (used & 0x5555) + ((used & 0xaaaa) >> 1);
4204 used = (used & 0x3333) + ((used & 0xcccc) >> 2);
4205 used = (used & 0x0f0f) + ((used & 0xf0f0) >> 4);
4206 used = (used & 0x00ff) + (used >> 8);
4207 const uint8_t *c = big5hkscs_to_charset[summary->index + used];
4208 if (c[1] != 0) {
4209 r[0] = c[0];
4210 r[1] = c[1];
4211 return 2;
4212 }
4213 else { // (c [1] == 0)
4214 r[0] = c[0];
4215 return 1;
4216 }
4217 }
4218 }
4219 return 0;
4220}
4221
4222static int qt_UnicodeToBig5(unsigned ch, uint8_t *buf)
4223{
4224 //all the tables are individually sorted on Y
4225 for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
4226 int start = 0;
4227 int end = b5_map_table[i].tableSize - 1;
4228
4229 while (start <= end) {
4230 int middle = (end + start + 1) / 2;
4231 if (b5_map_table[i].table[middle].y == ch) {
4232 buf[0] = b5_map_table[i].table[middle].x >> 8;
4233 buf[1] = b5_map_table[i].table[middle].x & 0xff;
4234 return 2;
4235 }
4236 else if (b5_map_table[i].table[middle].y > ch) {
4237 end = middle - 1;
4238 }
4239 else {
4240 start = middle + 1;
4241 }
4242 }
4243 }
4244 return qt_UnicodeToBig5hkscs(ch, buf);
4245}
4246
4247void
4248Big5TextEncoder::EncodeBig5(const std::wstring& str, std::string& bytes)
4249{
4250 static const char replacement = '?';
4251 //int invalid = 0;
4252
4253 bytes.resize(2 * str.length() + 1);
4254 int index = 0;
4255
4256 uint8_t c[2];
4257 for (wchar_t ch : str) {
4258 if (ch < 0x80) {
4259 // ASCII
4260 bytes[index++] = static_cast<char>(ch);
4261 }
4262 else if (qt_UnicodeToBig5(ch, c) == 2 && c[0] >= 0xa1 && c[0] <= 0xf9) {
4263 bytes[index++] = c[0];
4264 bytes[index++] = c[1];
4265 }
4266 else {
4267 bytes[index++] = replacement;
4268 //++invalid;
4269 }
4270 }
4271 bytes.resize(index);
4272}
